<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><refentry version="5.0-subset Scilab" xml:id="imbwhitmiss" xml:lang="en" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><refnamediv><refname>imbwhitmiss</refname><refpurpose>Apply binary hit-miss morphology.</refpurpose></refnamediv><refsynopsisdiv><title>Syntax</title><synopsis>out = imbwhitmiss(image, se); out = imbwhitmiss(image, se, iterations)</synopsis></refsynopsisdiv><refsection><title>Parameters</title><variablelist><varlistentry><term>image</term><listitem><para>Binary or numeric 2D image.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>se</term><listitem><para>Structuring element.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>iterations</term><listitem><para>Positive iteration count. Default is 1.</para></listitem></varlistentry></variablelist></refsection><refsection><title>Description</title><para><function>imbwhitmiss</function> is a MATLAB-style compatibility entry point for IPCV hit-miss morphology and returns a boolean mask.</para></refsection><refsection><title>Examples</title><programlisting><![CDATA[mask = zeros(7, 7) == 1; mask(3:5, 3:5) = %t; se = imcreatese("cross", 3, 3); out = imbwhitmiss(mask, se);]]></programlisting></refsection><refsection role="see also"><title>See also</title><simplelist type="inline"><member><link linkend="imhitmiss">imhitmiss</link></member><member><link linkend="imcreatese">imcreatese</link></member></simplelist></refsection><refsection><title>Authors</title><simplelist type="vert"><member>Tan Chin Luh</member></simplelist></refsection><refsection><title>History</title><informaltable border="1"><tr><td>Version</td><td>Description</td></tr><tr><td>5.0.0</td><td>Compatibility entry point introduced in development Step 3.</td></tr></informaltable></refsection></refentry>
